ce:section.ce:para:
Both bare CQDs and passivated CQDs (CQD–PEG1500N) were synthesized following the method reported in literature and concisely depicted in Fig. 1

                     [17]. Briefly, carbon nanoparticles were first refluxed in nitric acid with subsequent dialyzes against deionized water and centrifugation to retain the supernatant of smaller carbon nanoparticles, denoted in our studies as bare CQDs. Part of the bare CQDs was further treated in thionyl chloride for the succeeding reaction with oligomeric poly (ethylene glycol) diamine (PEG1500N). At the end of the reaction time, the mixture was cooled to room temperature, dispersed in deionized water and centrifuged at 25,000 g to retain the supernatant. The solution was further dialyzed against deionized water to remove the free functional moieties and finally obtain CQD–PEG1500N composites needed for our further electrical characterization. Morphological characterization of CQD–PEG1500N from HR-TEM revealed crystalline structures of 4–5 nm in diameter, comprising a stack of graphene layers (Fig. 2
                     ).
